label: Lake Champlain Islander
title: Lake_Champlain_Islander
exrest: The Islander is an American newspaper serving Grand Isle County, Vermont with an average circulation of 4,500 copies. A free weekly paper, it is published each Tuesday. The paper's circulation fluctuates throughout the year, peaking during the summer tourism season on the islands. The editor and owner is Tonya Poutry.
